title: The eno notation language and libraries

-- markdown
**eno** is a versatile data notation language for everyone, backed by open source libraries that help you build better and faster websites and applications around file-based content.

```eno
# Section

Field: Value (no quotes required ever)

List:
- Value
- Value

-- Multiline Field
Any long text or embedded content (e.g. markdown) here ...
-- Multiline Field

## Subsection
Field A: Value

# Section Copy < Section
Field: Replaced Value

# Section Deep Copy << Section
## Subsection
Field B: Added Value
```

**eno** is ...

As fast to write and edit as it probably gets - powerful and yet understandable for everyone (not just programmers).  
An excellent format for authoring entire websites, documentation, invoices, CVs, reports, configuration, you name it.  
Developer's bliss for quickly creating rich, reliable and production-ready user experiences around file-based content.

**eno** isn't ...

Arbitrary automatic data de/serialization - yaml, toml are made for, and excellent, at that.  
Human-readable inter-application/process communication - json is there and working great.

